<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="538" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,440,575]" pageId="15" pageNumber="538">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,512,539]" pageId="15" pageNumber="538">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Erect setae restricted to distal half or third of elytral margins; prothorax with lateral tubercles placed in the posterior third; antennae long and slender, 11-segmented. Number of species currently included: 20.
